{"title": "Phaedra", "description": "In the court of Louis XIV, adaptations of Greek tragedies were very popular. This play, heavily influenced by Euripides' Hippolytus, deals with love that violates social taboos. Note: In Racine's work, a new \"scene\" begins whenever a character enters or exits. Therefore, there are no stage directions, only a list of the characters on stage for each scene. The action is continuous for the entire act. (Summary by Libby Gohn)<br /><br />\n<strong>Cast</strong><br />\nNarrator: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/7848\">bala</a><br />\nTheseus: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/3699\">Bruce Pirie</a><br />\nPhaedra: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/1259\">Elizabeth Klett</a><br />\nHippolytus: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/7679\">Libby Gohn</a><br />\nAricia: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/7315\">Charlotte Duckett</a><br />\nOenone: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/6544\">Amanda Friday</a><br />\nTheramenes: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/7170\">Alan Mapstone</a><br />\nIsmene: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/8272\">Haili</a><br />\nPanope: <a href=\"http://librivox.org/reader/7766\">Maryanka</a><br /><br />\n<strong>Audio editing:</strong> Libby Gohn", "duration": 5932, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "992", "name": "Jean Racine"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt32/phaedra_1307.jpg", "copyright_year": "1677", "genres": ["Tragedy"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Libby Gohn"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Elizabeth Klett"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Charlotte Duckett"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Act I", "readers": [], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/phaedra_1306_librivox/phaedra_1_racine_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1304}, {"section": 2, "title": "Act II", "readers": [], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/phaedra_1306_librivox/phaedra_2_racin